# NestJS API Patterns

## Module structure

Every feature follows this layout:

```
modules/my-feature/
  my-feature.module.ts     — NestJS @Module, OnModuleInit for entity registration
  my-feature.controller.ts — REST endpoints
  my-feature.service.ts    — business logic
  my-feature.entity.ts     — TypeORM entity
  dto/
    create-my-feature.dto.ts
    update-my-feature.dto.ts
```

## Controllers

```ts
@ApiTags("my-feature")
@Controller("my-feature")
@UseGuards(AuthGuard, PermissionGuard)   // applied at class level
export class MyFeatureController {

  @Get()
  @RequirePermission("my_feature.read")
  findAll(@Actor() actor: ActorContext) { ... }

  @Post()
  @RequirePermission("my_feature.create")
  create(@Actor() actor: ActorContext, @Body() dto: CreateDto) { ... }
}
```

## Auth decorators

| Decorator | Location | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `@Public()` | method | skips AuthGuard (no JWT required) |
| `@RequirePermission("x.y")` | method | checked by PermissionGuard |
| `@RequireBranchScope()` | method | enforces X-Branch-Id header |
| `@Actor()` | parameter | injects `ActorContext` from JWT + header |

## ActorContext shape

```ts
interface ActorContext {
  userId: string;
  organizationId: string;
  branchId?: string;      // resolved from X-Branch-Id header or JWT
  roles: string[];
}
```

Always pass `actor.organizationId` / `actor.branchId` when scoping DB queries.

## DTOs

```ts
import { IsString, IsNotEmpty, IsOptional, IsNumber, Min } from "class-validator";
import { ApiProperty } from "@nestjs/swagger";

export class CreateItemDto {
  @ApiProperty({ example: "Áo thun" })
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  name: string;

  @ApiProperty({ required: false })
  @IsOptional()
  @IsNumber()
  @Min(0)
  sellingPrice?: number;
}
```

All DTOs validated by the global `ValidationPipe` (whitelist + transform + forbidNonWhitelisted).

## Generic CRUD entity registration

To expose an entity through the generic admin platform (`/admin/entities/:entityKey`):

```ts
// 1. Implement BaseCrudService<Entity, CreateDto, UpdateDto>
@Injectable()
export class MyEntityCrudService extends BaseCrudService<MyEntity, CreateDto, UpdateDto> {
  static readonly ENTITY_CONFIG: CrudEntityConfig = {
    entityKey: "my-entities",
    displayName: "Thực thể của tôi",
    apiResource: "/admin/entities/my-entities",
    idField: "id",
    fields: [
      { key: "name", label: "Tên", type: "string", required: true },
    ],
    searchableFields: ["name"],
    filterDefinitions: [],
    permissions: { read: "my_entity.read", create: "my_entity.create", ... },
    scopingPolicy: ScopingPolicy.ORGANIZATION,
    deletionPolicy: DeletionPolicy.SOFT,
  };
  // implement abstract methods: findAll, findOne, create, update, remove
}

// 2. Register in OnModuleInit
export class MyFeatureModule implements OnModuleInit {
  constructor(private registry: EntityRegistryService, private service: MyEntityCrudService) {}
  onModuleInit() {
    this.registry.registerEntity(
      MyEntityCrudService.ENTITY_CONFIG,
      MY_ENTITY_SERVICE_TOKEN,
    );
  }
}
```

The entity is then accessible at `/admin/entities/my-entities/records` and the backoffice route `/admin/my-entities` auto-renders a CRUD list page.

## Database rules

- `synchronize: false` always — never let TypeORM auto-sync in any environment
- All schema changes go through TypeORM migrations: `pnpm migration:generate`
- Monetary fields: `@Column({ type: "numeric", precision: 18, scale: 2 })`
- Soft-delete: `@DeleteDateColumn()` + `SoftDeleteEntity` base
- IDs: `@PrimaryGeneratedColumn("uuid")`
- Timestamps: `@CreateDateColumn()`, `@UpdateDateColumn()` (stored UTC)

## Events (Kafka/Redpanda)

```ts
// Inject EventPublisher (global provider)
constructor(private events: EventPublisher) {}

// Publish a typed event
await this.events.publish("inventory.item.created", {
  itemId: item.id,
  organizationId: actor.organizationId,
});
```

Topics are initialized in `TopicInitializer` on app start.
